```julia
using Dates: DateTime, Hour

function timezone_bumper(dt::DateTime, bump::Int=3)
    if dt + Hour(bump) > now()
        return error("The new timestamp is greater than the current time.")
    end
    return dt + Hour(bump)
end
```
This code defines a function `timezone_bumper` that accepts a DateTime object and an integer representing hours to bump (defaulting to 3). The function checks if the new timestamp is greater than the current time before returning it. If it is, an error is returned instead.
